he Earth's circumference, specifically one minute of latitude, which is why it's defined as 1852 meters. This definition was standardized internationally in 1959. \n\nSo, putting it all together, the answer is that one nautical mile is exactly 1852 meters, which is approximately 6076.12 feet.\n"},"done":true,"done_reason":"stop","total_duration":56553568833,"load_duration":6502495792,"prompt_eval_count":1332,"prompt_eval_duration":3422780542,"eval_count":157,"eval_duration":4987424418}
